HEADWORD: Bonanza
<hw>Bo*nan"za</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., prop. calm.,
fair weather, prosperity, fr. L. <ets>bonus</ets> good.]</ety> <def>In
mining, a rich mine or vein of silver or gold; hence, anything which is
a mine of wealth or yields a large income.</def> <mark>[Colloq. U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

